  "notes": [
    "PREPARATION FOR THE MINOR Complete the following: ECON 1: Introductory Microeconomics: Resource Allocation and Market Structure ECON 2: Introductory Macroeconomics: Aggregate Economic Activity STAT 17: Statistical Methods for Business and Economics AND STAT 17L: Statistical Methods for Business and Economics Laboratory Plus ONE of the following options: AM 11A: Mathematical Methods for Economists I AND AM 11B: Mathematical Methods for Economists II MATH 11A: Calculus with Applications AND MATH 11B: Calculus with Applications AND MATH 22: Introduction to Calculus of Several Variables MATH 19A: Calculus for Science, Engineering, and Mathematics AND MATH 19B: Calculus for Science, Engineering, and Mathematics AND MATH 23A: Vector Calculus MATH 19A: Calculus for Science, Engineering, and Mathematics AND MATH 19B: Calculus for Science, Engineering, and Mathematics AND AM 30: Multivariate Calculus for Engineers Please visit the Economics website to learn more about this minor.",
    "UC Santa Cruz students may choose to complete one or more minors, provided they can finish all required coursework within their maximum enrollment terms and allowable credits. While a minor will appear on a student's official transcript, it will not be listed on their diploma. Pursuing a minor is a personal decision that should align with a student's educational and career goals. Students do not apply for minors when submitting their application to UC Santa Cruz. After enrolling, transfer students interested in pursuing a minor should contact the department offering the minor for guidance."
